OVERVIEW
--------
Aurum is an autonomous AI credit bureau built on Casper Network. Six specialized
AI agents, orchestrated by LangGraph, generate verifiable on-chain credit profiles
for wallets. All agents use Groq-powered Llama 3.3 70B (temperature=0) with
rule-based fallback if the LLM call fails.

Current status: all 6 agents are live and operational. Smart contracts are
deployed on casper-test. CSPR.cloud wallet data is live. DeFi data (loans,
repayments, yield, RWA) falls back to empty lists because CSPR.cloud testnet
does not yet expose those endpoints.


================================================================================
  AGENT 1: CREDIT AGENT   (agents/credit_agent.py)
================================================================================

PURPOSE
-------
Generates credit scores (0-1000) using an XGBoost model with SHAP explainability.
This is the only fully deterministic agent — no LLM involved — so scores are
reproducible and auditable.

DATA SOURCES  (respects CSPR_CLOUD_MODE=live|mock)
------------
  cspr_cloud/wallet.py — WalletDataService
    get_wallet_volume_summary()  ->  tx_count, counterparty_diversity
    get_flow_summary()           ->  CSPR inbound / outbound breakdown
    get_liquidity_positions()    ->  active DeFi positions

  cspr_cloud/defi.py — DeFiDataService
    get_loan_records()           ->  loan history
    get_repayment_events()       ->  repayments made
    get_yield_events()           ->  yield/staking events (DAO proxy)
    get_rwa_events()             ->  real-world asset events

  Any service call failure is caught per-section; the failed dimension falls
  back to neutral 50 and the pipeline continues without halting.

SCORING DIMENSIONS  (each 0-100)
-----------------
  wallet_activity  = floor(tx_count / 2) + min(50, counterparty_diversity)
  repayment        = floor(repaid_count / max(loan_count, 1) * 100)  [50 if no loans]
  defi             = min(100, position_count * 20)
  income           = floor(inbound / max(inbound + outbound, 1) * 100)
  rwa              = min(100, rwa_event_count * 25)
  dao              = min(100, yield_event_count * 15)  [proxy for governance]

  -> XGBoost model.predict(features)  ->  credit_score (0-1000)
  -> SHAP explain_score(features)     ->  shap_breakdown

OUTPUTS
-------
  credit_score      int        0-1000
  sub_scores        dict       6 dimension scores
  shap_breakdown    dict       SHAP feature contribution per dimension
  raw_wallet_data   dict       all fetched service data (for downstream agents)

KNOWN LIMITATIONS
-----------------
  - defi, rwa, dao dimensions always score 0 in live mode because CSPR.cloud
    testnet has no confirmed loan/yield/RWA endpoints. wallet_activity,
    income, and repayment work live today.
  - wallet_age_days is not fetched directly; fraud agent uses a default of 180.


================================================================================
  AGENT 2: RISK AGENT   (agents/risk_agent.py)
================================================================================

PURPOSE
-------
Calculates default probabilities over 30/60/90-day horizons, assigns a risk tier,
and uses Groq LLM to identify early warning patterns beyond fixed thresholds.

WORKFLOW
--------
  1. Re-feed sub_scores into XGBoost model.predict_proba() -> base default prob
  2. Scale horizons:  60d = base * 1.5,  90d = base * 2.0  (capped at 0.99)
  3. Assign tier from credit_score:
       >= 750  ->  A (prime)
       >= 600  ->  B (near-prime)
       >= 450  ->  C (subprime)
       <  450  ->  D (high risk)
  4. Apply rule-based flags:
       repayment < 50          -> low_repayment_history
       default_prob_30d > 0.15 -> elevated_default_risk
       income < 40             -> inconsistent_income
       wallet_activity < 30    -> dormant_wallet
  5. Invoke Groq LLM (GROQ_API_KEY) with risk_analysis prompt
  6. Merge AI early_warnings with rule-based flags (deduped)
  7. Return tier, probs, merged warnings, and AI reasoning

  LLM FALLBACK: if LLM fails, returns rule-based flags only with
  risk_analysis = "Rule-based analysis only"

OUTPUTS
-------
  risk_tier             str    A / B / C / D
  default_prob_30d      float  rounded to 3 decimal places
  default_prob_60d      float
  default_prob_90d      float
  early_warning_flags   list   merged rule + AI flags
  risk_analysis         str    AI narrative or fallback label

GROQ KEY
--------
  Uses GROQ_API_KEY (shared instance via AgentLLM)


================================================================================
  AGENT 3: FRAUD AGENT   (agents/fraud_agent.py)
================================================================================

PURPOSE
-------
AI-powered fraud detection. Analyzes raw_wallet_data for wash trading, sybil
indicators, circular transactions, and fresh-wallet risk.

WORKFLOW
--------
  1. Extract wallet_age_days from raw_wallet_data (default 180 if missing)
  2. Build fraud_detection prompt with wallet profile from raw_wallet_data
  3. Invoke Groq LLM (GROQ_API_KEY)
  4. Parse JSON: { fraud_score, fraud_flags, reasoning, confidence }

  LLM FALLBACK (rule-based):
    wallet_age_days < 7         -> fresh_wallet_sybil_risk  (+0.2)
    daily_avg_tx > 5            -> high_transaction_frequency  (+0.1)
    counterparty_diversity < 3  -> low_counterparty_diversity  (+0.15)
    fraud_score = sum of above, capped at 1.0
    fraud_confidence = 0.7 (conservative)

OUTPUTS
-------
  fraud_score       float  0.0 - 1.0
  fraud_flags       list   detected pattern labels
  fraud_reasoning   str    AI explanation or fallback label
  fraud_confidence  float  0.0 - 1.0

GROQ KEY
--------
  Uses GROQ_API_KEY


================================================================================
  AGENT 4: ATTESTATION AGENT   (agents/attestation_agent.py)
================================================================================

PURPOSE
-------
Aggregates all agent outputs into a signed attestation, saves to Supabase, and
submits real on-chain deploys (issue_credit_score + issue_compliance_token) to
Casper testnet when AURUM_DEPLOY_MODE=live.

WORKFLOW
--------
  1. Invoke Groq LLM (GROQ_API_KEY_1) with attestation_summary prompt
  2. Build attestation_payload with all assessment data + timestamp
  3. db.save_attestation(payload) -> attestation_hash (Supabase URL)
  4. Compute:
       default_prob_bps  = int(default_prob_30d * 10000)
       borrowing_limit   = tier_limits[risk_tier]  (A=100T, B=50T, C=10T, D=1T motes)
       has_aml_flag      = "aml" in fraud_flags
       compliance_level  = "restricted" if aml else "basic"

  5a. AURUM_DEPLOY_MODE=live:
       submitter.submit_contract_call(
           CreditRegistry, "issue_credit_score",
           { caller, borrower, score, tier, default_probability_bps,
             borrowing_limit_motes, attestation_hash, issued_at, expiry_at }
       )
       submitter.submit_contract_call(
           ComplianceRegistry, "issue_compliance_token",
           { caller, borrower, level, aml_flag, issued_at, expiry_at }
       )
       tx_hash = deploy_hash from credit deploy result
       deploy_mode = "live"  (or "live_failed" on exception)

  5b. AURUM_DEPLOY_MODE=mock:
       builds contract call envelope dicts via contracts.py
       tx_hash = "mock-deploy-{wallet[:16]}-{timestamp}"
       deploy_mode = "mock"

  NOTE: attestation agent calls submitter.submit_contract_call() directly,
  bypassing the contracts.py envelope layer, for the live write path.

OUTPUTS
-------
  attestation_hash          str   Supabase record URL
  tx_hash                   str   deploy hash (live) or mock string
  attestation_summary       str   AI-generated professional summary
  deploy_mode               str   "live" | "mock" | "live_failed"
  credit_deploy_result      dict  (live only) full submit result
  compliance_deploy_result  dict  (live only) full submit result
  borrowing_limit_motes     int
  compliance_level          str   "basic" | "restricted"

GROQ KEY
--------
  Uses GROQ_API_KEY_1


================================================================================
  AGENT 5: MONITORING AGENT   (agents/monitoring_agent.py)
================================================================================

PURPOSE
-------
Decides whether the freshly-issued credential should be active or revoked.
Reads the most recent previous assessment from Supabase for context.

WORKFLOW
--------
  1. get_assessment(wallet_address) from Supabase (previous record if any)
  2. Build credential_monitoring prompt with current score/tier/fraud/default
  3. Invoke Groq LLM (GROQ_API_KEY)
  4. Parse JSON: { credential_active, reasoning, action }

  LLM FALLBACK:
    default: credential_active=True, action="maintain"
    if fraud_score > 0.5: credential_active=False, action="revoke"

  NOTE: This agent only sets the monitoring_action flag. Actual on-chain
  revocation is handled by routers/cron.py (POST /cron/monitor), which calls
  submitter.submit_contract_call(CreditRegistry, "revoke_credit_score", ...)
  in live mode.

OUTPUTS
-------
  credential_active     bool   True = keep, False = revoke
  monitoring_reasoning  str    AI explanation or fallback label
  monitoring_action     str    "maintain" | "monitor" | "revoke"

GROQ KEY
--------
  Uses GROQ_API_KEY


================================================================================
  AGENT 6: LENDING AGENT   (agents/lending_agent.py)
================================================================================

PURPOSE
-------
Matches the borrower's risk tier to available lending pool offers and uses
Groq LLM to generate a personalized loan recommendation.

POOL OFFERS  (hardcoded, mock protocol data)
-----------
  Tier A  ->  TrueFi    8%   up to $50,000
  Tier B  ->  Maple     12%  up to $20,000
  Tier C  ->  Clearpool 18%  up to $5,000
  Tier D  ->  no offers

WORKFLOW
--------
  1. Look up offers for risk_tier
  2. If tier D: return early with empty loan_offers
  3. Build lending_recommendation prompt
  4. Invoke Groq LLM (GROQ_API_KEY_1)
  5. Parse recommendation string

  LLM FALLBACK: "Tier {tier} offers available at market rates."

OUTPUTS
-------
  loan_offers             list  available pool offers for tier
  lending_recommendation  str   AI-personalized advice or fallback

GROQ KEY
--------
  Uses GROQ_API_KEY_1

KNOWN LIMITATIONS
-----------------
  Pool rates and limits are hardcoded. No live protocol integration.
  TrueFi, Maple, and Clearpool are illustrative — not real API connections.


================================================================================
  PIPELINE ORCHESTRATION   (pipeline/graph.py)
================================================================================

EXECUTION FLOW
--------------
  Credit -> Risk -> Fraud -> Attestation -> Monitoring -> Lending -> END

  Linear, no conditional branching. Each agent receives the full PipelineState
  TypedDict and returns an updated copy. State accumulates all outputs.

LANGGRAPH STRUCTURE
-------------------
  StateGraph(PipelineState)
  set_entry_point("credit")
  add_edge: credit->risk, risk->fraud, fraud->attestation,
            attestation->monitoring, monitoring->lending, lending->END

INVOCATION
----------
  from pipeline.graph import pipeline
  result = pipeline.invoke({"wallet_address": "e1b7c7..."})

API KEY DISTRIBUTION
--------------------
  GROQ_API_KEY   ->  Fraud, Risk, Monitoring (via AgentLLM singleton cache)
  GROQ_API_KEY_1 ->  Attestation, Lending

  Two keys prevent rate-limit exhaustion. AgentLLM caches instances by key
  name so each key gets one ChatGroq instance reused across calls.


================================================================================
  SHARED UTILITIES   (agents/utils/llm_utils.py)
================================================================================

AgentLLM
--------
  get_llm(key_name)            Returns cached ChatGroq(model="llama-3.3-70b-versatile",
                               temperature=0) for the given env var key name
  invoke_llm(llm, prompt)      HumanMessage call + parse_json_response
  parse_json_response(resp)    Strips markdown code fences, parses JSON.
                               Returns None on JSONDecodeError.

Prompts
-------
  fraud_detection(wallet, data, score)         -> JSON: fraud_score, flags, reasoning, confidence
  risk_analysis(score, tier, prob, sub_scores) -> JSON: early_warnings, risk_analysis, recommendation
  attestation_summary(wallet, score, tier, ..) -> JSON: summary
  credential_monitoring(wallet, score, tier,..)-> JSON: credential_active, reasoning, action
  lending_recommendation(score, tier, prob,..) -> JSON: recommendation

  All prompts request JSON responses. Temperature=0 ensures deterministic output.


