================================================================================
  ON-CHAIN INTEGRATION   (casper/)
================================================================================

WRITE PATH (AURUM_DEPLOY_MODE=live)
-----------------------------------
  Attestation agent calls casper/deploy_submitter.DeploySubmitter directly:
    submit_contract_call(contract_hash, entrypoint, args)
    -> casper-client put-deploy --session-hash <hex> --session-entry-point <ep>
    -> returns { success, deploy_hash }

  Cron monitor calls DeploySubmitter for revoke_credit_score:
    POST /cron/monitor -> pipeline.invoke() -> if action=="revoke":
      submitter.submit_contract_call(CreditRegistry, "revoke_credit_score",
        { caller, borrower, revoked_at })

  All entrypoints take an explicit "caller" string (deployer account-hash)
  as their first argument.

READ PATH (AURUM_DEPLOY_MODE=live)
----------------------------------
  contracts.AurumContracts.get_credit_score(borrower) uses call_getter():
    submit_contract_call(get_score) + poll 60s + _extract_return_value()
  Similarly: is_compliant(), get_reputation(), query_credit_profile()

  NOTE: The oracle router (/oracle/query) reads from Supabase as the primary
  low-latency cache. call_getter() is used for cross-validation only.

